g","31.4 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["This exotic Middle Eastern dish is bursting with fresh, vibrant flavours and textures. Tender lamb seasoned with Turkish chilli flakes is rolled in buttery puff pastry, then baked until golden and crisp. Served with freekeh, an ancient, protein-rich grain with an earthy, nutty flavour, this impressive main would make a great choice next time you’re entertaining friends or family.","Use low-fat mince, otherwise too much fat may leak out during cooking causing the pastry to become soggy.","Try to use Urfa chilli flakes, if available. These flakes have a very particular taste - smoky, sweet, earthy but not too spicy.","To make your own puff pastry, follow the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>.","This recipe also works with filo pastry - wrap in <b>6 large<b> sheets. Brush with melted butter and reduce cooking time slightly."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 5m","8 portions"]}